  "prompt": "Does all the questions get answered in Quora?",
  "response": "No, not all questions on Quora get answered. Several factors influence whether a question receives a response:\n\n1. Popularity/Interest Level\n- Some questions attract more attention and are more likely to be answered\n- Niche or highly specific questions might remain unanswered\n\n2. Question Quality\n- Clearly written and well-structured questions are more likely to get answers\n- Vague or poorly worded questions may be ignored\n\n3. Topic Relevance\n- Questions in popular topics or with broad appeal tend to get more responses\n- Specialized or technical questions might have fewer potential respondents\n\n4. Community Engagement\n- The size and activity of the specific topic's community matters\n- Some topics have more active contributors than others\n\n5. Timing\n- Recently asked questions have a higher chance of getting answers\n- Very old or outdated questions might not attract responses\n\n6. User Interest\n- Answers depend on experts or people interested in the specific topic\n- Not all topics have knowledgeable users willing to respond\n\nWhile Quora has a large user base, it doesn't guarantee that every single question will receive a comprehensive or satisfactory answer. The platform's response rate varies across different topics and question types.",
